You are building 'Wallet' — a macOS menu bar app using Electron + React + Tailwind.

PRODUCT CONTEXT:
Wallet stores 8 personal context cards (Identity, Voice, Expertise, Current Work,
Audience, Aesthetic, Narrative, Goals) and injects them into AI tools automatically.
It is NOT a finance app, credentials wallet, or general notes app.

ARCHITECTURE:
- Electron main process: menubar package, electron-store for persistence
- React renderer: Vite + Tailwind v4
- Context detection: osascript polling (no native deps)
- IPC via contextBridge preload
- MCP server: Node.js sidecar for Claude Desktop

DESIGN SYSTEM (always use these, never raw hex values):
- Colors: wallet-bg, wallet-surface, wallet-panel, wallet-purple, wallet-cyan, etc.
- Glass treatment: glass class with backdrop-filter
- Gradient: wallet-purple → wallet-cyan for CTAs and active states
- Dark mode only — no light mode support
- Mono text: .mono class for metadata, tags, timestamps

CODE STYLE:
- TypeScript strict
- Functional React components
- No class components
- Shared types in src/shared/
- Main process types duplicated for CommonJS compat

NEVER:
- Use light mode styles
- Hard-code hex colors (use Tailwind tokens)
- Add native dependencies that need compilation
- Use require() in renderer (ESM only)
